{"type":"message","id":"fd2ed3c8","parentId":"8527c229","timestamp":"2026-05-11T03:08:30.346Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Since the MCP service returned that the user is not logged in, I need to get a QR code for login. However, this is a cron job running automatically - there's no one to scan the QR code. \n\nLet me think about this differently. The cron job is set up to push 小红书 content to 飞书. The issue is the 小红书 MCP isn't logged in. \n\nOptions:\n1. Tell the user about this in the cron result summary\n2. Try to get the QR code and see if it saves an image that can be shown to the user\n\nSince this is a cron job that runs automatically, I should just report the status in the summary. The user needs to scan the QR code manually first to log in.\n\n\nI'll generate the QR code and include it in the summary output so they can scan it to resolve the login issue."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_owj2ja55qqft_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd \"C:\\Users\\linkang\\.openclaw\\workspace\"; python xhs_login.py 2>&1","timeout":60}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778468897475}}
